Package: LibeRties
Type: Package
Title: Portable Job Execution for LibeR
Version: 0.7.0
Authors@R: person("Sven C.", "van Dijkman",
    email = "svdijkman@users.noreply.github.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Author: Sven C. van Dijkman [aut, cre]
Maintainer: Sven C. van Dijkman <svdijkman@users.noreply.github.com>
Description: Executes serialized LibeR simulation and estimation jobs in
    restricted subprocesses with isolated per-user working directories. A persistent cross-platform local queue uses
    background R worker processes and the same versioned job contract intended
    for remote Linux servers. Payload checksums, explicit state transitions,
    metadata locking, safe path components, cancellation, logs, restart
    recovery, per-tenant quotas, monitored resource limits, and result
    provenance are built into the contract. Production deployments require an
    external operating-system isolation layer and TLS termination.
